  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc2\u0bb1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 : \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd : \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0ba9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Can't say the day of the ship's arrival: Do not wait in line: Minister Kanchana",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Fuel prices have risen again in about a month by the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation. The price hikes are effective from 2 am on Sunday (26).",
        "The price of 92 octane petrol has been increased by 50 rupees. After the price increase, the new price is 470 rupees.",
        "Similarly, the price of octane 95 petrol has been increased by 100 rupees. The new price is 550 rupees.",
        "The price of a liter of diesel has also been increased by 60 rupees. The new price is 460 rupees. Similarly, the price of super diesel has been increased by 75 rupees. Its price has risen to 520 rupees.",
        "Fuel prices rose similarly on May 24. Octane 92 petrol was priced at 82 rupees, octane 95 petrol at 77 rupees, Otto diesel at 111 rupees and super diesel at 116 rupees.",
        "Despite the increase in prices, people are still unable to get unrestricted access to fuel.",
        "The queues to get fuel day by day are also getting longer. Minister of Power and Energy Kanchana Wijesekera has asked the public not to wait in line unnecessarily as the next date of fuel ships cannot be ascertained in such a situation.",
        "Minister of Power and Energy Kanchana Wijesekera has said that the import companies have informed the Petroleum Corporation that their arrival has been delayed due to factors including banking activities, despite earlier announcements by the importers that petrol, diesel and lubricants would arrive in two weeks.",
        "Therefore, until the next fuel ships arrive in the country, the Minister said that fuel will be distributed with priority to public transport, power generation and industry.",
        "The minister also asked the public not to wait in queues unnecessarily as diesel and petrol will be distributed to petrol stations on a limited basis this week.",
        "At present it is not possible to say for sure when the fuel ships will arrive in the country. It is noteworthy that Minister Kanjana Wijesekera has stated that the operations of the refinery will be temporarily suspended until the next lubricant arrives in the country."
      ],
